            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Your requests currently exceed the capacity for the number of First Aid Attendant FAA or Floor Emergency Officers FEO needed to be onsite. FAA and FEO have been advised that the maximum capacity has been reached and that the organization requires a minimum of one more volunteer to be onsite.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">According to the <a style="background-color: transparent; color: #00627e; text-decoration: underline;" href="https://laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/l-2/page-14.html#h-341197">Canada Labor Code, part II</a>, the OPC have legal obligations to have sufficiant trained FAA or FEO to be on site at all times during operational hours.</p>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Your request is currently pending, until an FEO or FAA will make their reservation. You will receive a confirmation when your request will be approved.</p>
